# Documentation Rules

## Core Doctrine
- KnowledgeOS is the internal source of truth.
- The website is a curated rendering surface.
- Avoid duplication: link to canonical notes.

## Structure for Durable Notes
1. Frontmatter
2. H1 title
3. Summary callout
4. Body sections
5. Related Notes
6. TODOs

## Quality Bar
- Scannable in under 60 seconds for overview notes.
- Runbooks must include preconditions, steps, validation, rollback.
- Indexes/registries use tables with stable IDs.

## Cross-System Docs
- When documenting website publishing, reference `src/content/` and `docs/templates/`.
- When documenting infra, reference [[ARCHITECTURE]].

## AI Behavior
- Update existing notes before creating near-duplicates.
- Keep enterprise tone.
- Preserve wikilinks and frontmatter.
